FIVE-FOLD PETERSEN MAP: EXCEPTIONAL GROUPS ON K(5,2)
======================================================================

Petersen K(5,2) has 10 vertices and 15 edges
Each vertex = {i,j} subset of {0,1,2,3,4}
Edge connects {i,j} and {k,l} iff disjoint (i.e., {i,j,k,l} = 4 elements)

